# Exclude modtable from HTML validity checks (ESLint and the Mustache checks
# still run, and every other template here stays fully validated).
#
# modtable is a page fragment, not a standalone document: its checkboxes carry
# form="tool_timelocker_form", which points at the moodleform rendered earlier
# on the page (see classes/form/timelocker_form.php). The linter renders the
# template on its own, where no such form exists, so the HTML validator always
# reports "The form attribute must refer to a form element" for markup that is
# correct on the real page.
modtable.mustache
